==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paleëchinoidea
<hw>Pa`le*⟦eum⟧ch`i*noi"de*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Paleo-</er>, and <er>Echinoidea</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An extinct order of sea urchins found in the
Paleozoic rocks. They had more than twenty vertical rows of plates.
Called also <altname>Palaeechini</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Palaeechinoidea</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>paleencephalon</ent>⟦br⟧
